main event: A civilian observed unidentified objects in Duluth, Minnesota, on 14 November 1969, for approximately 10 minutes.
interesting points: The photographic evidence is heavily redacted and obscured, making it difficult to identify the objects., The report contains multiple descriptions of the shape and motion of the unidentified objects., Observations included irregular movements and blinking lights of the unidentified objects., The sighting had a maximum observation elevation of about 10 degrees above the horizon., Witness descriptions were recorded as compelling but lacked clarity due to the quality of the photographs.
witness description: A civilian observer who reported seeing unidentified objects.
